title: For Sale/Trade:  D-Technik SA VZ-58 w/accessories
postcontent:
I'm getting out of the 7.62x39 caliber, so up for sale is my beloved VZ 58.  This is an original import from D-Technik, via Tennessee Guns Int'l, purchased in 2008.  For those of you who don't know, it's not an AK.  It's a proprietary system developed by Czechoslovakia during the cold war, using the 7.62x39 cartridge.  It's action is a short-stroke piston, akin to the German STG-44 more than the AK-47 and it's variants.  The receiver is milled, versus stamped like an AK, resulting in a lighter weight.  There are more differences, which you can research online if you care to.  Let's get to the rifle and accessories. 
SA VZ-58 7.62x39, chrome lined barrel with milled receiver (this is not a Century VZ2008 build, but the real mccoy)
approx 200 rounds down the pipe, very little use and meticulously maintained
Folding stock, with UTG grenade launcher buttpad (for greater LOP on short stock)
Troy Industries Aluminum railed forend (Mako polymer forend included if you want it)
Fab pistol grip
NEA tactical bolt release
Pinned/welded Czech military brake
mag parts kits x10
700 rounds ammo, mixed Tula, Wolf, etc steel cased.  300 of which is on stripper clips.
Sturdy nylon replica of chicom chest rig, carries all 300 rounds with stripper clips.

I have over $1500 into this rifle, with ammo and accessories.  I'm asking $1100.

title: For Sale:  Beautiful Colt 1st Generation SAA 38 Special 1901
postcontent: This Colt 1st Generation SAA was manufactured around 1901 and originally chambered in 38-40. Prior to WWII it was sent back to Colt and converted to fire 38 Spcl which was very popular at the time. The conversion is still 1st Generation as it was done in the late 1930's prior to the start of WWII. This particular revolver has an interesting family history, but I am selling it due to some urgent financial needs. The condition of this Colt is very good to excellent and it should be both a fantastic shooter as well as fine collectible at a reasonable price due to the conversion. This revolver has a 5 1/2" barrel and the bore looks great. Nice Colts like this are getting very hard to find so don't miss out. As with all older firearms this revolver must be checked out by a competent gunsmith prior to firing it. Buyer to pay actual shipping and provide copy of FFL.

title: For Sale:  Pre-Ban Israeli Heavy Barrel Shorty FAL Paratrooper
postcontent: For sale I have a Pre-Ban Israeli Heavy Barrel Paraptrooper. This Rifle was built on an imbel receiver. The person I got this from told me they purchased it in the 80s and it was an original imported Israeli Rifle and I'm still not sure it isn't but I've had a few extremely rude emails by immature children calling me stupid for posting what I was told by the previous owner in calling this a pre-ban Israeli Paratrooper which is exactly what it is. I don't know anything else about it except for what I'm posting and I know the receiver is pre-ban making the rifle itself pre-ban because all post ban imbel receivers were required to have the date stamped in the magwell and this one doesn't making it a pre-ban. If you research Imbel you will find that their quality is equal to that of original FN Belgian FALs. This rifle was built using a 16.25" Israeli Heavy Barrel. It appears original to me and doesn't appear like it was cutdown. The reason I believe it's an original 16.25" Israeli HB is because of the Milled cut for the bipod which would have been cut off if the barrel was originally a full length 24" Israeli HB. It's definitely possible it could have been cut and a portion of the barrel was milled out for the bipod but if that was done it was an expert job because I can't tell. The previous owner said he took off the original bipod and flashider because he didn't like them and he was unable to find them when he sold it to me. Luckily these are easy parts to find on various sights such as gunbroker or eBay. The barrel is Israeli marked and dated 5/67 where the barrel goes into the receiver. It shoots great and is extremely accurate for such a short barrel which I attribute to the abnormally thick and heavy barrel. I have never even seen another picture of one of these in this configuration let alone seen one for sale so I don't have another one to compare it to but I do have another heavy barrel full size Israeli rifle and the barrel on this paratrooper is noticeably thicker the barrel is really a monster. Rifle will come with one 30 round magazine and 5 20 round magazines and another set of Israeli HB Hanguards which are painted black to match the rest of the rifle. The added extras alone are worth over $200 so it's a nice bonus. I have over $2000 invested in this rifle so my asking price is pretty firm. With normal pre ban Fals running over $1500 now this is a hell of a bargain. Only trade I would consider would be for a Browning 1919 belt fed in .308/7.62. I can add some cash if need be. E-mail, Call, or text REDACTED. I will ship anywhere in the US but it must go to an FFL License Holders address and I will need a copy of an FFL E-mailed to me for my records.
